The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Cape Town to host first match
                                                   Cape Town to host first match
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The opening match of the second edition of the Indian Premier League, it is understood, will be played between Chennai Super Kings and Mumbai Indians in Cape Town on April 18. In the second match of the day, Royal Challengers Bangalore will face Rajasthan Royals.         
	It was also learnt that there will be eight venues for the league and every team will get to play everywhere. The eight venues are Durban, Johannesburg, Pretoria, Cape Town, East London, Bloemfontein, Kimberley and Port Elizabeth. The tickets will be on sale within the next 48 hours.         
	Both the semi-finals and the final will be held at the Wanderers in Johannesburg.                                                                                                                       
